Description: Unidentified artefact of faience, quite thin, showing remains of a light green glaze, one undecorated flat side, opposite a slightly bended area with a black horizontal line and two further lines in a v-like shape joining the line in the pointed part; a third preserved part slightly curved, might show another line, possibly part of a vessel.
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
